        "content": "openPDS: A Privacy-Preserving Personal Data Store.  With their built-in sensors, smartphones are at the forefront of personal data collection. However, personal data currently tends to be monopolized and siloed preventing companies to built innovative data-driven services. While there is substantial work on privacy and fair use of personal data, a pragmatic technical solution has yet to be realized. openPDS is a privacy-preserving implementation of an information repository which allows the user to collect, store, and give access to his data. Via",
